## Design Decisions Log

### Why Prisma over TypeORM?
- Better TypeScript support
- Type-safe query API
- Migration system more reliable
- Active development and community

### Why Feature-Based Structure?
- Scales better for large teams (reduced merge conflicts)
- Clear ownership boundaries
- Easier to extract microservices later
- Aligns with domain-driven design

### Why Server Components First?
- Better performance (no client JS by default)
- Simpler code (no useState/useEffect boilerplate)
- SEO-friendly by default
- Direct database access without API layer

## Performance Considerations

### Server Components
- Use for data fetching
- Cache with `revalidate` option
- Minimize client JavaScript

### Client Components
- Use sparingly (only for interactivity)
- Code split with dynamic imports
- Optimize bundle size

### Database Queries
- Add indexes for frequently queried fields
- Use `select` to fetch only needed fields
- Implement pagination for large datasets

## Security Best Practices

- Validate all API inputs with Zod
- Use Server Actions for mutations
- Implement rate limiting on API routes
- Never expose database credentials
- Use environment variables for secrets
